{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block title %}Import Turo CSV - Turo Tracker{% endblock %}
{% block content %}

<h2>Import Turo Trip Earnings</h2>

<div class="import-box">
  <p>Upload the CSV export from Turo's Host Tools &rarr; Earnings page. Each trip becomes an income transaction on the matching car, using Turo's "Total earnings" figure (already net of fees, discounts, and Turo's service fee).</p>

  <ol>
    <li>In Turo, go to Earnings and export your trip history as CSV.</li>
    <li>Upload it below.</li>
    <li>Match vehicles to your cars and pick which trips to import.</li>
  </ol>

  <form method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
    <div class="file-input">
      <input type="file" name="csv_file" accept=".csv" required>
    </div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn">Upload &amp; Preview</button>
  </form>

  <p>Re-uploading a file that overlaps a previous import is safe — trips already imported (matched by reservation ID) will be updated in place, not duplicated.</p>
</div>

{% endblock %}
